name: The Queen's Palaces
overview: Fiona Bruce fronts this eye-opening new three-part series on the stories behind Britain's official royal residences: Buckingham Palace, Windsor Castle and Palace of Holyroodhouse.

episodes.name: Buckingham Palace
episodes.overview: Buckingham Palace, the British monarch's present principal official residence, in London, was originally built as a hunting lodge by Tudor King Henry VIII.

episodes.name: Windsor Castle
episodes.overview: Windsor Castle was built not as a palace but retains the massive walls of a major military fortification, erected while Anglo-Norman England absorbed its Celtic neighbors

episodes.name: Palace of Holyroodhouse
episodes.overview: The Palace of Holyroodhouse in Edinburgh is the British monarch's barely known official residence in Scotland.
